This makes cs.NE a possible category.

4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper does not seem to be related to social or information networks, but it is possible that the authors have used network analysis techniques to study the subsurface system. This makes cs.SI a possible category.

5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper does not seem to be focused on data structures or algorithms, but it is possible that the authors have used specific algorithms to develop the reduced-order models. This makes cs.DS a possible category.
